{"key":"post-9771193","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9771193</id>\n<content>I've used all sorts of terrariums with clear and white lids.&amp;nbsp; In fact, the tek on the DVD shows two different terrariums under construction, one with a white lid just to show they work OK.&amp;nbsp; Side light is fine.&amp;nbsp; If it disturbs anyone to see mushrooms growing towards the light, all you have to do is rotate your terrarium every day or two, and they'll balance out.&amp;nbsp; In fact, you can rotate it 90 degrees every day and get spiral mushrooms. &lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/smileys/laugh.gif&quot; alt=&quot;:laugh:&quot; title=&quot;:laugh:&quot;/&gt;&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9771420</next>\n<prev>9770882</prev>\n<first>9770712</first>\n<last>9771583</last>\n<when>1234283352</when>\n<utime>02/10/09 06:29 PM</utime>\n</post>"}